stylometry: RISKSIMTABLE allows you to run multiple simulations at once for certain values, usually the decision variable. In a simulation model, you can have a various number of "numbers/orders to try." When running the simulation, you can then view the mean, median, mode, standard deviation, etc. of the various number of simulations. An example of a simulation model is figuring out how many servers you need in a restaurant. You can run a simulation on 8 servers, 10 servers, 12 servers, etc. After running the simulation, you can use RISKSIMTABLE to view their mean, median, mode, standard deviation, etc, to make the best possible decision.
